# UDS Master Workflow

## SYNC FIRST ‚Äî Source-of-truth check ‚Äî Change ‚Äî Finalize

Four-phase workflow. The pre-migration "Phase 3: BUMP first" step is
gone ‚Äî the SITE-versioning apparatus (`bump-site.sh`, `version.txt`)
was deleted in Chunk 17 of the Next.js migration. Changelog writing
still happens, but as part of Phase 5's finalize step rather than as
a preflight bump.

### Phase 1: BEFORE anything ‚Äî verify sync state with origin

Before reading rules or starting work, confirm the local repo is current
with `origin/main`. Cloud-agent edits to `.cursor/rules/`,
`.cursor/skills/`, or `.cursor/agents/` made on `main` will be invisible
to a local agent until pulled ‚Äî which means the local agent can read a
stale rule and act on outdated guidance without knowing.

The `sessionStart` Cursor hook at `.cursor/hooks/sync-check.sh` runs
this check automatically at the start of every session. It writes the
canonical state file at `.cursor/state/sync-status.json` (always, even
when in sync) AND best-effort emits an `additional_context` warning per
Cursor's documented hook output schema.

The state file is the source of truth ‚Äî `additional_context` injection
has had reported reliability issues for `sessionStart` hooks in past
Cursor versions. So always read the file:

```bash
cat .cursor/state/sync-status.json
```

If `status` is `behind` or `diverged`, STOP and pull before any other
work, using the `recommendedPull` value from the state file:

- `git pull --ff-only origin main` if local has no diverging commits
- `git pull --rebase origin main` if local has work to preserve

Then re-read any rule/skill/agent file you've already loaded in this
session ‚Äî your previous read may have been stale.

If the hook didn't run for any reason (Cursor ran without hooks, the
state file is missing, or its `writtenAt` timestamp is older than the
session start), run it manually:

```bash
git fetch --quiet origin && git status -sb
```

The companion artifacts:
- [`.cursor/TOOLCHAIN.md`](../TOOLCHAIN.md) ‚Äî inventory of every rule,
  skill, and subagent with ISO 8601 UTC `lastUpdated` per file. Use it
  for a fast "what changed in the instruction layer since I last
  looked?" scan.
- [`uds-rule-discipline.mdc`](./uds-rule-discipline.mdc) ‚Äî what to
  do AFTER editing a rule/skill/subagent (lastUpdated bump, TOOLCHAIN
  regenerate). Enforced by `scripts/audit-toolchain-currency.sh`.

### Phase 2: BEFORE you start ‚Äî is this even your call?

If the request is going to modify any file under **`uds-docs/uds/`**
(tokens, component CSS, spec.json, examples, schemas, status.json,
changelog.json, impl.json, components.json, version.json), stop and
re-read `.cursor/rules/uds-source-of-truth.mdc`. That directory is
Figma's source of truth and is almost never agent-modifiable; the
authorized write paths are the named Figma-sync skills
(`import-figma-tokens`, `sync-figma-component-spec`,
`sync-figma-component-status`, `link-figma-nodes`, `new-component`) or
an explicit user-directed revert toward verified Figma parity. If the
work doesn't fit one of those, surface findings rather than apply
edits.

This check sits BEFORE Phase 3 on purpose ‚Äî there's no point editing
the docs site if the proposed change shouldn't happen at all.

### Phase 3: Make the actual changes

Now do whatever the user asked for. Edit React components, CSS,
per-component JSON, etc.

The SITE-versioning preflight from the pre-migration workflow is
deleted. Cache-busting is now Cloudflare's job (per
`uds-docs/public/_headers`); per-asset content hashing is Next's job
(`_next/static/*` is content-addressed by default).

### Phase 4: Finalize ‚Äî canonical component-update round-trip checklist

After all changes are complete, run THIS exact checklist. Every named
Figma-sync skill (`sync-figma-component-spec`, `sync-figma-component-status`,
`link-figma-nodes`, `import-figma-tokens`, `new-component`) references this
section as its definition of "done." Do not duplicate the steps inside the
skill files; do them here.

1. **Add a `SITE_CHANGELOG` entry** in
   `uds-docs/data/site-changelog.ts` describing what changed. Follow
   [`uds-site-changelog.mdc`](./uds-site-changelog.mdc) for the entry
   shape and the voice/length contract. The pre-migration "stub
   first, fill in later" pattern is gone ‚Äî there's no preflight bump
   anymore, so write the real entry as part of finalize.
2. **Per-component changelog entry** ‚Äî if you edited any file under
   `uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/` (`<id>.css`, `spec.json`,
   `status.json`, `examples/**`, `impl.json`, `playground.js`) or the matching
   Web Component / React wrapper source, you MUST add
   a corresponding entry to `uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/changelog.json` for
   the current UDS version. The only exemption is a pure revert toward
   verified Figma parity; in that case include `[no-changelog: revert toward
   Figma parity]` in the commit message and the `scripts/audit-changelog-currency.sh`
   audit will skip the component.
3. **Aggregate** ‚Äî if you changed any per-component `changelog.json` or
   `uds/CHANGELOG.globalNotes.json`, run
   `bash scripts/aggregate-changelog.sh`. If you added or removed a
   component folder, also run `bash scripts/aggregate-components.sh`.
   `scripts/audit-aggregate-currency.sh` will fail CI if you skip this.
4. **Figma sync-state snapshot** ‚Äî if the change was sourced from a Figma
   read (a Figma-sync skill ran, or you manually corrected `figmaNodeId` /
   `figmaPageNodeId` after a direct inspection), update
   `.cursor/figma/state/components.snapshot.json` (the relevant component's
   `componentSetNodeId`, `pageNodeId`, `variantProperties`,
   `nestedInstances`) and `.cursor/figma/state/last-sync.json` (bump
   `lastSuccessfulSync`, recompute `components.snapshotChecksum`).
   `scripts/audit-figma-sync-state-currency.sh` will fail CI if `spec.json`
   `figmaNodeId` / `figmaPageNodeId` disagree with the snapshot.
5. **Figma Release Notes sync** ‚Äî if `uds/CHANGELOG.json` changed (whether
   via a release or via mid-release per-component changelog additions), run
   the `sync-figma-release-notes` skill to rebuild the `Release Notes` frame
   on the `UDS Version: X.Y` page in BOTH `UDS Tokens` and `UDS Components`
   Figma files. Both files must contain identical text. This is allowed
   write scope #1 per `.cursor/rules/uds-figma-write-safety.mdc`.
6. **Cache busting** ‚Äî no manual cache-bust steps post-migration.
   Cloudflare's `_headers` (in `uds-docs/public/_headers`) handles
   short-TTL revalidation for runtime JSON, and Next.js content-hashes
   its own static assets. If you edit `_headers`, mention that in the
   SITE_CHANGELOG entry.
7. **Token-first CSS** ‚Äî for any new CSS added under `uds-docs/uds/**`,
   verify it uses `--uds-*` tokens (no hardcoded colors, font sizes,
   spacings, radii). `scripts/audit-token-usage.sh` enforces this.
8. **Component contract** ‚Äî if a component was added or modified, verify
   it satisfies `uds-component-checklist.mdc`: class, anatomy, variants,
   required states or explicit `notApplicable` reasons, Web Component API,
   React wrapper API, examples, playground controls, accessibility, and the
   complete per-component folder (`<id>.css`, `spec.json`, `status.json`,
   `changelog.json`, `impl.json`, `playground.js`,
   `examples/manifest.json`, ‚â•1 example HTML); sidebar link in
   `uds-docs/components/site/SiteSidebar.tsx` for new public components.
   `scripts/audit-component-completeness.sh` enforces the per-folder
   completeness; the sidebar link is a manual check (the file is
   structure-as-data, one new line per added component).
9. **Content schema** ‚Äî if you edited a component's spec, verify it was
   JSON-side at `uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/spec.json`. The Guidelines
   tab is rendered from that JSON by
   `uds-docs/app/(site)/[componentId]/GuidelinesTab.tsx`.
10. **Agent-toolchain bookkeeping** ‚Äî if you edited any file under
    `.cursor/rules/`, `.cursor/skills/`, or `.cursor/agents/` (added,
    renamed, removed, or changed content):
    - Bump that file's `lastUpdated:` in its YAML frontmatter to the
      current ISO 8601 UTC timestamp. Use `date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ`
      ‚Äî never guess. Format must match the precedent set by
      `.cursor/figma/state/last-sync.json` `lastSuccessfulSync`.
    - Run `bash scripts/regenerate-toolchain.sh` to deterministically
      rebuild `.cursor/TOOLCHAIN.md` from frontmatter. Do NOT hand-edit
      the index ‚Äî your edits will be overwritten on the next regenerate.
    - If the change affected the file's purpose or description, mirror
      it in
      [`uds-docs/app/(site)/cursor-workflows/page.tsx`](../../uds-docs/app/(site)/cursor-workflows/page.tsx)
      in the same commit.

    Two audits enforce this:

    - `scripts/audit-toolchain-currency.sh` ‚Äî fails if any file's
      `lastUpdated` is older than its git mtime, if any file is missing
      a row in `TOOLCHAIN.md`, or if any row date disagrees with the
      file's frontmatter.
    - `scripts/audit-agent-docs-currency.sh` ‚Äî fails if a
      rule/skill/subagent file exists but isn't referenced on
      `cursor-workflows.html` (or the reverse). Internal-only artifacts
      that intentionally aren't on the page belong in
      `scripts/audit-baseline.json`
      `audit-agent-docs-currency.toleratedFiles`.

    See [`uds-rule-discipline.mdc`](./uds-rule-discipline.mdc) for the
    standalone rule that auto-attaches when you edit any of these files.

## Why this order matters

The pre-migration version of this rule had a Phase 3 "BUMP first" step
that ran `bump-site.sh` before any edits. That script (and the entire
SITE-versioning apparatus ‚Äî `version.txt`, the `?v=N` cache-bust query
params, the runtime auto-reload poller) was deleted in Chunk 17 of the
Next.js migration. Cloudflare handles cache invalidation (per
`uds-docs/public/_headers`), and Next.js content-hashes its own static
assets ‚Äî there's nothing for an agent to bump.

The other finalize-time discipline is preserved and is enforced by CI
audits, not just convention:

- `scripts/audit-changelog-currency.sh` ‚Äî fails if a component's source files
  (CSS/spec/examples/impl/playground/Web Component source/React wrapper) have newer commits than
  `changelog.json`.
- `scripts/audit-aggregate-currency.sh` ‚Äî fails if `uds/CHANGELOG.json` or
  `uds/components.json` differs from a fresh aggregate.
- `scripts/audit-figma-sync-state-currency.sh` ‚Äî fails if any `spec.json`
  `figmaNodeId` disagrees with `components.snapshot.json` `componentSetNodeId`.
- `scripts/audit-css-api-table.sh` ‚Äî legacy-named audit that now treats empty
  `cssClasses` arrays as intentional for Web Components and fails only when
  documented API data drifts from retained component payload CSS.
- `scripts/audit-doc-internal-consistency.sh` ‚Äî per-component doc-side
  coherence safety net (the partner of the `figma-component-inspector`'s
  bidirectional Surplus pass). Four checks: orphan `.udc-<id>*` CSS
  selectors absent from every example/impl/playground/API-data entry;
  spec `events[]` not dispatched in `@uds/web-components` source (DOM-native
  events auto-excused); `impl.json` token refs missing from
  `uds/tokens/*.css`; `commonlyPairedWith[]` refs missing from
  `components.json`. Catches partial cleanups (e.g. you removed a CSS
  rule but left the slot in `spec.json`). Tolerated findings are
  enumerated in `scripts/audit-baseline.json`
  `audit-doc-internal-consistency.toleratedFindings`; new drift fails.
- `scripts/audit-agent-docs-currency.sh` ‚Äî fails if a rule/skill/subagent
  file under `.cursor/` exists but isn't referenced on the
  `cursor-workflows` page
  (`uds-docs/app/(site)/cursor-workflows/page.tsx`), or vice-versa (the
  page references a deleted file). Baseline-grandfathered via
  `scripts/audit-baseline.json`.
- `scripts/audit-toolchain-currency.sh` ‚Äî fails if any
  rule/skill/subagent file's frontmatter `lastUpdated:` is older
  (date-only) than the file's git mtime, if any file is missing a
  row in `.cursor/TOOLCHAIN.md`, or if any row's date doesn't match
  the file's frontmatter exactly. Three checks bundled.
